Paramedics say they discovered the man lying on the pavement surrounded by bystanders after the shooting earlier on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - A man has been shot and wounded in Olievenhoutbosch, in Centurion. Paramedics say they discovered the man on a pavement. He was surrounded by bystanders after the shooting  on Tuesday. The man has been hospitalised and is in a critical condition. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said: “The man was treated for his injuries and provided with advanced life support interventions. Once treated, the man was transported to Kalafong Provincial Hospital for urgent treatment.”